Build a production-quality local web application: a Kubernetes/OpenShift log explorer designed for stable, predictable debugging using a snapshot + refresh model (NO live streaming by default), with a high-quality modern UI/UX.

---

🧱 Tech Stack (STRICT)

Frontend

- React (Vite)
- TypeScript
- TailwindCSS
- shadcn/ui
- Zustand
- react-window

Backend

- Node.js (LTS)
- Express
- child_process.spawn (for "oc")
- NO WebSockets
- NO external logging systems

---

🎯 CORE PRINCIPLE

«Stability + readability + control over updates»

---

🧭 DATA FLOW (STRICT)

1. "oc get projects"
2. "oc get deployments -n <project>"
3. "oc get pods -n <project>"
4. Single pod selection ONLY

🚨 NEVER mix logs from multiple pods

---

🧠 DATA MODEL

Initial load

oc logs <pod> -n <project> --tail=<N>

Refresh

oc logs <pod> -n <project> --since-time=<lastSeenTimestamp>

---

🎨 UI / UX (CRITICAL — HIGH PRIORITY)

🔤 Typography (VERY IMPORTANT)

- Logs font: JetBrains Mono
- UI font: Inter
- Font size MUST be readable:
  - Logs: 13–15px minimum (NOT smaller)
  - Line height: comfortable (1.5+)
- No dense/compressed UI
- Prioritize readability over density

---

🧱 LAYOUT STRUCTURE

🔝 Top Bar (GLOBAL CONTROL BAR)

Contains:

- 🔍 Search input (PRIMARY FEATURE)
- Toggle: Regex mode (on/off)
- Log level filters (chips/buttons)
- Refresh button
- Auto-refresh toggle
- Interval selector

---

🔍 SEARCH SYSTEM (TOP BAR)

- Instant filtering
- Supports:
  - plain text search
  - ✅ regex mode (toggle)
- Highlight matches in logs
- Case sensitive toggle (optional)

---

📂 LEFT DRAWER (NAVIGATION PANEL)

A collapsible drawer from the left side

Contains:

- Project (searchable dropdown)
- Deployment (searchable dropdown)
- Pod (searchable dropdown)
- Tail selector

Rules:

- Dropdowns MUST support search (typeahead)
- Clean spacing, not cramped
- Clear hierarchy

---

📄 RIGHT DRAWER (LOG INSPECTOR — KIBANA STYLE)

Opens when clicking a log

Contains:

1. Structured JSON viewer

- Expandable tree
- Syntax highlighted

2. Raw log view

3. Metadata panel

- timestamp
- project
- pod
- log level

4. Actions

- copy raw
- copy JSON
- copy field

Drawer behavior:

- slides from right
- resizable (optional)
- closable

---

🟢 MAIN LOG VIEW

- Center panel
- Virtualized list
- Stable (NO auto-scroll)

Each log line:

#10421  2026-04-30T09:12:33Z  INFO  message...

---

🔢 LOG NUMBERING

- Sequential index
- Continues across refresh
- Resets on pod change

---

🟡 NEW LOGS INDICATOR

+37 new logs  [Show]

Rules:

- Appears when new logs fetched
- Clicking “Show” scrolls to bottom
- No automatic scroll

---

🔵 SCROLL BEHAVIOR

- NEVER auto-scroll
- Preserve user position
- “Jump to latest” button

---

🧠 INTERACTION RULES

- UI must NEVER shift unexpectedly
- No layout jumps
- No flicker
- Smooth updates only

---

🔍 FEATURES

Filtering

- text search
- regex search
- log level filter

---

Highlighting

- ERROR → red
- WARN → yellow
- INFO → blue
- DEBUG → gray

Keywords:

- error
- timeout
- failed
- exception

---

⚠️ EDGE CASES

Duplicate logs

- remove on merge

High volume

⚠️ Some logs may have been skipped

---

🚫 CONSTRAINTS

- NO streaming UI
- NO infinite scroll
- NO multi-pod logs
- NO complex grouping engines

---

📦 OUTPUT

Generate:

1. Backend (Node.js)
   
   - projects / deployments / pods
   - logs (tail)
   - refresh (since-time)

2. Frontend (React)
   
   - top bar with search + regex
   - left drawer (selectors)
   - right drawer (log inspector)
   - stable log viewer
   - readable typography

3. Zustand state

4. Architecture explanation

5. Run instructions

---

🎯 FINAL GOAL

A clean, modern developer tool that:

- feels like Kibana but lighter
- is readable and not dense
- never loses user position
- gives full control over logs

